k on Y?\" questions.\n\nArgs:\n    query: Search query (e.g. \"knowledge graph implementation\", \"OCR receipt scanning\")\n    n_results: Number of results (default 5)\n    project: Filter by project name (e.g. \"my-app\", \"backend\")\n"), input_schema: {"properties": Object {"n_results": Object {"default": Number(5), "title": String("N Results"), "type": String("integer")}, "project": Object {"anyOf": Array [Object {"type": String("string")}, Object {"type": String("null")}], "default": Null, "title": String("Project")}, "query": Object {"title": String("Query"), "type": String("string")}}, "required": Array [String("query")], "title": String("session_searchArguments"), "type": String("object")}, output_schema: Some({"properties": Object {"result": Object {"items": Object {"additionalProperties": Bool(true), "type": String("object")}, "title": String("Result"), "type": String("array")}}, "required": Array [String("result")], "title": String("session_searchOutput"), "type": String("object")}), annotations: None, icons: None, meta: None }, Tool { name: "codegraph_query", title: None, description: Some("Execute a raw Cypher query against the code intelligence graph.\n\nThe graph contains: Project, File, Symbol, Package, Session nodes.\nEdges: HAS_FILE, DEFINES, DEPENDS_ON, MODIFIED, IN_PROJECT, TOUCHED, EDITED, CREATED,\n       IMPORTS (File->File or File->Package), CALLS (File->Symbol), INHERITS (Symbol->Symbol).\n\nExample queries:\n  - MATCH (p:Project) RETURN p.name, p.path LIMIT 10\n  - MATCH (f:File {project: 'my-app'}) RETURN f.path, f.lang LIMIT 20\n  - MATCH (p:Project)-[:DEPENDS_ON]->(pkg:Package) WHERE pkg.name = 'react' RETURN p.name\n  - MATCH (s:Session)-[:EDITED]->(f:File) RETURN f.path, COUNT(s) ORDER BY COUNT(s) DESC LIMIT 10\n\nArgs:\n    query: Cypher query string\n"), input_schema: {"properties": Object {"query": Object {"title": String("Query"), "type": String("string")}}, "required": Array [String("query")], "title": String("codegraph_queryArguments"), "type": String("object")}, output_schema: Some({"properties": Object {"result": Object {"items": Object {"additionalProperties": Bool(true), "type": String("object")}, "title": String("Result"), "type": String("array")}}, "required": Array [String("result")], "title": String("codegraph_queryOutput"), "type": String("object")}), annotations: None, icons: None, meta: None }, Tool { name: "codegraph_stats", title: None, description: Some("Get code intelligence graph statistics.\n\nReturns counts of projects, files, symbols, packages, sessions,\nand edge type breakdown.\n"), input_schema: {"properties": Object {}, "title": String("codegraph_statsArguments"), "type": String("object")}, output_schema: None, annotations: None, icons: None, meta: None }, Tool { name: "codegraph_explain", title: None, description: Some("Architecture overview of a project from the code graph.\n\nReturns structured data: stack, languages, directory layers, key patterns\n(mixins, base classes, CRUD schemas), top dependencies, and hub files.\n\nArgs:\n    project: Project name (e.g. \"my-app\", \"backend-api\")\n"), input_schema: {"properties": Object {"project": Object {"title": String("Project"), "type": String("string")}}, "required": Array [String("project")], "title": String("codegraph_explainArguments"), "type": String("object")}, output_schema: None, annotations: None, icons: None, meta: None }, Tool { name: "codegraph_repomap", title: None, description: Some("Generate a YAML-formatted repository map showing the most important files and their symbols.\n\nHelps understand the global structure of a project without reading all files.\n\nArgs:\n    project: Project name (e.g. \"my-app\")\n    limit: Maximum number of top files to include (default 20)\n"), input_schema: {"properties": Object {"limit": Object {"default": Number(20), "title": String("Limit"), "type": String("integer")}, "project": Object {"title": String("Project"), "type": String("string")}}, "required": Array [String("project")], "title": String("codegraph_repomapArguments"), "type": String("object")}, output_schema: None, annotations: None, icons: None, meta: None }, Tool { name: "codegraph_shared", title: None, description: Some("Packages shared across multiple projects in the code graph.\n\nReturns list of packages with the projects that depend on them,\nsorted by number of projects (most shared first).\nUseful for finding common dependencies and potential shared infrastructure.\n"), input_schema: {"properties": Object {}, "title": String("codegraph_sharedArguments"), "type": String("object")}, output_schema: Some({"properties": Object {"result": Object {"items": Object {"additionalProperties": Bool(true), "type": String("object")}, "title": String("Result"), "type": String("array")}}, "required": Array [String("result")], "title": String("codegraph_sharedOutput"), "type": String("object")}), annotations: None, icons: None, meta: None }, Tool { name: "project_info", title: None, description: Some("Get project information from the registry.\n\nWithout name: returns list of all active projects with stacks.\nWith name: returns detailed info for one project.\n\nArgs:\n    name: Project name (e.g. \"my-app\"). Omit for full list.\n"), input_schema: {"properties": Object {"name": Object {"anyOf": Array [Object {"type": String("string")}, Object {"type": String("null")}], "default": Null, "title": String("Name")}}, "title": String("project_infoArguments"), "type": String("object")}, output_schema: Some({"properties": Object {"result": Object {"anyOf": Array [Object {"items": Object {"additionalProperties": Bool(true), "type": String("object")}, "type": String("array")}, Object {"additionalProperties": Bool(true), "type": String("object")}], "title": String("Result")}}, "required": Array [String("result")], "title": String("project_infoOutput"), "type": String("object")}), annotations: None, icons: None, meta: None }, Tool { name: "web_search", title: None, description: Some("Search the web via SearXNG (Tavily-compatible API).\n\nUses smart engine routing: auto-selects engines based on query keywords.\nOverride with engines param for specific sources.\n\nEngine groups (auto-detected):\n  - academic: arxiv, google scholar (keywords: research, paper, algorithm)\n  - tech: github, stackoverflow (keywords: python, react, code, framework)\n  - product: brave, reddit, app stores (keywords: app, competitor, pricing, vs)\n  - news: google news, hacker news (keywords: news, latest, 2026, trend)\n  - general: google, duckduckgo, brave, reddit (default fallback)\n\nArgs:\n    query: Search query\n    max_results: Number of results (default 10)\n    engines: Override engine selection (e.g. \"reddit\", \"hacker news\", \"arxiv,google scholar\")\n    include_raw_content: Include full page content (up to 5000 chars per page)\n"), input_schema: {"properties": Object {"engines": Object {"anyOf": Array [Object {"type": String("string")}, Object {"type": String("null")}], "default": Null, "title": String("Engines")}, "include_raw_content": Object {"default": Bool(false), "title": String("Include Raw Content"), "type": String("boolean")}, "max_results": Object {"default": Number(10), "title": String("Max Results"), "type": String("integer")}, "query": Object {"title": String("Query"), "type": String("string")}}, "required": Array [String("query")], "title": String("web_searchArguments"), "type": String("object")}, output_schema: None, annotations: None, icons: None, meta: None }, Tool { name: "web_fetch", title: None, description: Some("Fetch a URL with browser-like headers to bypass basic bot protection.\n\nReturns page content as plain text (HTML tags stripped) or raw HTML.\nHandles redirects, cookies, and common anti-bot headers automatically.\n\nArgs:\n    url: URL to fetch\n    max_length: Max content length in chars (default 20000)\n    extract_text: Strip HTML tags and return plain text (default true)\n    timeout: Request timeout in seconds (default 30)\n"), input_schema: {"properties": Object {"extract_text": Object {"default": Bool(true), "title": String("Extract Text"), "type": String("boolean")}, "max_length": Object {"default": Number(20000), "title": String("Max Length"), "type": String("integer")}, "timeout": Object {"default": Number(30), "title": String("Timeout"), "type": String("integer")}, "url": Object {"title": String("Url"), "type": String("string")}}, "required": Array [String("url")], "title": String("web_fetchArguments"), "type": String("object")}, output_schema: None, annotations: None, icons: None, meta: None }, Tool { name: "project_code_search", title: None, description: Some("Semantic search over project source code and documentation.\n\nSearches indexed project codebases (per-project FalkorDB vector DBs).\nAuto-indexes the project on first search if no index exists.\nUseful for finding code patterns, functions, classes, and docs across projects.\n\nArgs:\n    query: Search query (e.g. \"authentication middleware\", \"API route handler\")\n    n_results: Number of results (default 5)\n    project: Project name or path (e.g. \"my-app\", \"~/projects/my-app\"). Omit to search all.\n    chunk_type: Filter by \"code\" or \"doc\"\n"), input_schema: {"properties": Object {"chunk_type": Object {"anyOf": Array [Object {"type": String("string")}, Object {"type": String("null")}], "default": Null, "title": String("Chunk Type")}, "n_results": Object {"default": Number(5), "title": String("N Results"), "type": String("integer")}, "project": Object {"anyOf": Array [Object {"type": String("string")}, Object {"type": String("null")}], "default": Null, "title": String("Project")}, "query": Object {"title": String("Query"), "type": String("string")}}, "required": Array [String("query")], "title": String("project_code_searchArguments"), "type": String("object")}, output_schema: Some({"properties": Object {"result": Object {"items": Object {"additionalProperties": Bool(true), "type": String("object")}, "title": String("Result"), "type": String("array")}}, "required": Array [String("result")], "title": String("project_code_searchOutput"), "type": String("object")}), annotations: None, icons: None, meta: None }, Tool { name: "project_code_reindex", title: None, description: Some("Reindex a project's source code and docs into FalkorDB vectors.\n\nCall this after significant code changes to update the search index.\nUses sentence-transformers backend (safe for memory).\n\nArgs:\n    project: Project name or path (e.g. \"my-app\", \"~/projects/my-app\")\n"), input_schema: {"properties": Object {"project": Object {"title": String("Project"), "type": String("string")}}, "required": Array [String("project")], "title": String("project_code_reindexArguments"), "type": String("object")}, output_schema: None, annotations: None, icons: None, meta: None }, Tool { name: "source_search", title: None, description: Some("Search indexed external sources (Telegram, YouTube, etc.).\n\nEach source is stored in its own FalkorDB graph.\nYouTube videos are chunked by chapters — results include chapter name and timecode.\nWithout source filter, searches all sources and merges by relevance.\n\nArgs:\n    query: Search query (e.g. \"startup idea\", \"revenue growth\")\n    source: Filter by source name (e.g. \"telegram\", \"youtube\"). Omit to search all.\n    n_results: Number of results (default 5)\n"), input_schema: {"properties": Object {"n_results": Object {"default": Number(5), "title": String("N Results"), "type": String("integer")}, "query": Object {"title": String("Query"), "type": String("string")}, "source": Object {"anyOf": Array [Object {"type": String("string")}, Object {"type": String("null")}], "default": Null, "title": String("Source")}}, "required": Array [String("query")], "title": String("source_searchArguments"), "type": String("object")}, output_schema: Some({"properties": Object {"result": Object {"items": Object {"additionalProperties": Bool(true), "type": String("object")}, "title": String("Result"), "type": String("array")}}, "required": Array [String("result")], "title": String("source_searchOutput"), "type": String("object")}), annotations: None, icons: None, meta: None }, Tool { name: "source_tags", title: None, description: Some("List all auto-detected topics with video counts.\n\nTags are assigned automatically via zero-shot embedding similarity\nduring video indexing. Shared across videos — enables topic clustering.\n\nArgs:\n    source: Source name (default: \"youtube\")\n"), input_schema: {"properties": Object {"source": Object {"default": String("youtube"), "title": String("Source"), "type": String("string")}}, "title": String("source_tagsArguments"), "type": String("object")}, output_schema: Some({"properties": Object {"result": Object {"items": Object {"additionalProperties": Bool(true), "type": String("object")}, "title": String("Result"), "type": String("array")}}, "required": Array [String("result")], "title": String("source_tagsOutput"), "type": String("object")}), annotations: None, icons: None, meta: None }, Tool { name: "source_related", title: None, description: Some("Find related videos by shared tags.\n\nGiven a video URL, finds other videos that share auto-detected topics.\nReturns videos sorted by number of shared tags (most related first).\n\nArgs:\n    video_url: YouTube video URL or video ID\n    source: Source name (default: \"youtube\")\n"), input_schema: {"properties": Object {"source": Object {"default": String("youtube"), "title": String("Source"), "type": String("string")}, "video_url": Object {"title": String("Video Url"), "type": String("string")}}, "required": Array [String("video_url")], "title": String("source_relatedArguments"), "type": String("object")}, output_schema: Some({"properties": Object {"result": Object {"items": Object {"additionalProperties": Bool(true), "type": String("object")}, "title": String("Result"), "type": String("array")}}, "required": Array [String("result")], "title": String